cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use confident-extract in your research or production system, please cite it as below."
type: software
title: "confident-extract"
abstract: >
  confident-extract is a Python library for deterministic structured extraction from noisy
  LLM and OCR output. It repairs malformed JSON without additional LLM calls, validates
  against msgspec Structs, Pydantic v2 BaseModel subclasses, and Python dataclasses, and
  returns a confidence score reflecting the structural quality of the original input.
authors:
  - family-names: "Desai"
    given-names: "Hitarth"
    alias: "hitarthbuilds"
repository-code: "https://github.com/hitarthbuilds/confident-extract"
url: "https://pypi.org/project/confident-extract/"
license: MIT
version: "0.1.0"
date-released: "2026-06-20"
keywords:
  - structured extraction
  - LLM output parsing
  - JSON repair
  - schema validation
  - msgspec
  - pydantic
  - orjson
  - natural language processing
  - information extraction
  - machine learning
